18
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:35,000
And I personally believe by
avoiding these eight things,

19
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:37,750
you'll have a much higher
chance of becoming rich.

20
00:00:37,750 --> 00:00:38,780
Hi guys, it's Mark.

21
00:00:38,780 --> 00:00:40,200
So let's make money interesting

22
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:41,890
so that you can grow your wealth.

23
00:00:41,890 --> 00:00:44,089
First up, we have extended warranties.

24
00:00:44,089 --> 00:00:47,100
I have to say, they're one of
the biggest scams out there.

25
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:49,680
Well, apart from the Squid
Game token, that's for sure.

26
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:52,360
I learned this when I bought
my first method of transport,

27
00:00:52,360 --> 00:00:55,210
a Yamaha DT100 motorbike.

28
00:00:55,210 --> 00:00:57,260
I paid for an extended warranty,

29
00:00:57,260 --> 00:01:00,220
which they added to the
monthly payments of the bike.

30
00:01:00,220 --> 00:01:02,570
Every month they were
feeding on my bank account,

31
00:01:02,570 --> 00:01:04,370
like some sort of vampire.

32
00:01:04,370 --> 00:01:05,380
The worst thing of all is

33
00:01:05,380 --> 00:01:07,360
I didn't need the extended warranty,

34
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:09,310
but the salesman use fear tactics

35
00:01:09,310 --> 00:01:11,280
to pressure me into purchasing it.

36
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:12,200
Just think about it.

37
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:13,500
When you buy a new PC,

38
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:15,900
the chances are the retailer bought the PC

39
00:01:15,900 --> 00:01:17,800
from a third-party supplier.

40
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:20,880
Meaning the amount of profit
they make is very small.

41
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:22,160
That's why it makes sense for them

42
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:24,550
to push an extended warranty onto you.

43
00:01:24,550 --> 00:01:26,570
It's where all the extra profit is made.

44
00:01:26,570 --> 00:01:29,040
What people seem to forget
is a lot of credit cards

45
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:30,910
offer an extended warranty.

46
00:01:30,910 --> 00:01:33,430
So you can just purchase
an item on your credit card

47
00:01:33,430 --> 00:01:35,260
to get the same protection,

48
00:01:35,260 --> 00:01:36,890
and you pay no interest

49
00:01:36,890 --> 00:01:39,360
as long as you pay off at the
end of every month in full.

50
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:41,110
Most people would just completely forget

51
00:01:41,110 --> 00:01:42,840
that they have an extended warranty,

52
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:44,340
not to mention the fine print,

53
00:01:44,340 --> 00:01:46,830
which usually makes it
very hard to make a claim.

54
00:01:46,830 --> 00:01:49,670
So as good as throwing
your money down the drain.

55
00:01:49,670 --> 00:01:52,170
Normally they ask you if you
want a three-year warranty.

56
00:01:52,170 --> 00:01:55,360
However, the manufacturers cover
the first two years anyway.

57
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:58,770
So the reality is you're only
buying an extra year anyway.

58
00:01:58,770 --> 00:02:01,440
So honestly, when you factor
in your consumer rights

59
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:03,830
and using a credit card
for payment protection,

60
00:02:03,830 --> 00:02:06,070
why would you need an extended warranty?

61
00:02:06,070 --> 00:02:08,280
I bet a lot of shops don't
want you to know this.

62
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:10,200
Number two is new cars.

63
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:11,870
What if I told you that a new car

64
00:02:11,870 --> 00:02:15,300
